    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A decorative feature in Gothic architecture, carved in a variety of leaf shapes and projecting at regular intervals from the angles of spires, gables, or capitals. A decorative feature in Gothic architecture, carved in a variety of leaf shapes and projecting at regular intervals from the angles of spires, gables, or capitals.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000096407/Concise Oxford Dictionary of Art Terms [online] (2001-2008)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>En arquitectura gótica y derivadas, ornamentos salientes normalmente en forma vegetal, a menudo regularmente espaciados a lo largo de los bordes de grandes caracterizaciones, tales como aguilones, o usado sobre capiteles.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Uitstekende ornamenten meestal met vegetale vorm, vaak regelmatig verdeeld langs randen van grotere elementen zoals gevels of gebruikt op kapitelen. Komt voor in de gotische architectuur en daarvan afgeleide vormen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
